      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) comparison against in vitro blood damage measurements",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) derived from Lagrangian particle tracking and power-law hemolysis model compared against in vitro NIH measurements across five flow-speed operating conditions. Mean NIH predictions fall within the range of experimental replicates. Inherent variability in blood damage response attributed to donor-to-donor biological variation and batch-to-batch reagent differences was assessed qualitatively by the engineering team during review; a structured uncertainty quantification node capturing aleatory spread in measured NIH values was not formally linked to this result."
    },
